“Because he got such an order, he threw them

00:57:33.804 --> 00:57:35.806 line:90% position:50% align:center
“into the inner prison

00:57:35.806 --> 00:57:38.600 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and fastened their feet in the stocks.

00:57:40.519 --> 00:57:43.022 line:90% position:50% align:center
“But about the middle of the night,

00:57:43.022 --> 00:57:45.107 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Paul and Silas were praying

00:57:45.107 --> 00:57:48.277 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and praising God with song,

00:57:48.277 --> 00:57:50.904 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the prisoners were listening to them.”

00:57:53.073 --> 00:57:55.284 line:90% position:50% align:center
What do you think made them want to sing?

00:57:59.246 --> 00:58:00.998 line:90% position:50% align:center
They loved Jehovah.

00:58:00.998 --> 00:58:04.335 line:90% position:50% align:center
And when they focused on that,
how do you think they felt?

00:58:09.757 --> 00:58:10.924 line:90% position:50% align:center
I think

00:58:13.469 --> 00:58:15.512 line:90% position:50% align:center
they felt some peace.

00:58:15.512 --> 00:58:16.555 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s right.

00:58:17.765 --> 00:58:20.142 line:90% position:50% align:center
How about we dig a little bit deeper?

00:58:20.893 --> 00:58:21.435 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK.

00:58:21.602 --> 00:58:22.144 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK.

00:58:27.691 --> 00:58:29.735 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, what did you notice?

00:58:30.819 --> 00:58:34.823 line:90% position:50% align:center
Gabe and Olivia are under pressure

00:58:34.823 --> 00:58:39.620 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Olivia in the classroom,
Gabe at the witnessing cart.

00:58:40.829 --> 00:58:44.124 line:90% position:50% align:center
How will they handle the pressure

00:58:44.124 --> 00:58:48.379 line:90% position:50% align:center
in a way that preserves
their peace with Jehovah?

00:58:49.463 --> 00:58:52.132 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, it’s a good question.

00:58:52.132 --> 00:58:54.927 line:90% position:50% align:center
And really, all of us

00:58:54.927 --> 00:58:57.721 line:90% position:50% align:center
need to reflect on that question

00:58:57.721 --> 00:59:00.391 line:90% position:50% align:center
when we’re under pressure.

00:59:00.391 --> 00:59:03.602 line:90% position:50% align:center
We know that Jehovah’s way is the best way.

00:59:03.602 --> 00:59:08.273 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’re convinced that his way of ruling
is the best way.

00:59:10.234 --> 00:59:13.195 line:90% position:50% align:center
But when we’re subjected to pressure,

00:59:13.195 --> 00:59:17.866 line:90% position:50% align:center
perhaps the victim of some injustice

00:59:17.866 --> 00:59:20.244 line:90% position:50% align:center
or even of some evil,

00:59:21.829 --> 00:59:26.750 line:90% position:50% align:center
we may be inclined
to take matters into our own hands.

00:59:28.293 --> 00:59:31.296 line:90% position:50% align:center
And when we do,

00:59:31.296 --> 00:59:34.466 line:90% position:50% align:center
it can jeopardize our peace.

00:59:35.968 --> 00:59:40.222 line:90% position:50% align:center
So how do we demonstrate respect

00:59:40.222 --> 00:59:42.933 line:90% position:50% align:center
for Jehovah’s sovereignty?

00:59:42.933 --> 00:59:47.062 line:90% position:50% align:center
The inspired advice
in Romans chapter 12 can help.

00:59:47.062 --> 00:59:50.399 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s look together at Romans chapter 12,

00:59:50.399 --> 00:59:52.734 line:90% position:50% align:center
beginning in verse 17:

00:59:56.071 --> 00:59:59.741 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Return evil for evil to no one.”

00:59:59.741 --> 01:00:04.746 line:90% position:50% align:center
So this provides the context
for what follows.

01:00:04.746 --> 01:00:07.875 line:90% position:50% align:center
We may suffer some evil.

01:00:07.875 --> 01:00:11.128 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Return evil for evil to no one.

01:00:11.128 --> 01:00:16.008 line:90% position:50% align:center
Take into consideration what is fine
from the viewpoint of all men.”

01:00:16.008 --> 01:00:18.469 line:90% position:50% align:center
And then notice verse 18:

01:00:18.469 --> 01:00:21.513 line:90% position:50% align:center
“If possible, as far as it depends

01:00:21.513 --> 01:00:24.057 line:90% position:50% align:center
“on you,

01:00:24.057 --> 01:00:29.021 line:90% position:50% align:center
be peaceable (be a peacemaker)
with all men.”

01:00:30.898 --> 01:00:32.941 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, these words

01:00:32.941 --> 01:00:36.069 line:90% position:50% align:center
really heighten our appreciation

01:00:36.069 --> 01:00:39.531 line:90% position:50% align:center
for Jehovah’s reasonableness.

01:00:39.531 --> 01:00:42.409 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why do we say that?

01:00:42.409 --> 01:00:44.453 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because Jehovah doesn’t ask us

01:00:44.453 --> 01:00:48.373 line:90% position:50% align:center
to do something that we can’t do.

01:00:48.373 --> 01:00:52.169 line:90% position:50% align:center
He doesn’t ask us to control others.

01:00:52.169 --> 01:00:54.171 line:90% position:50% align:center
No,

01:00:55.255 --> 01:01:00.219 line:90% position:50% align:center
to the extent “it depends on you.”

01:01:00.219 --> 01:01:02.888 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah asks that each of us

01:01:02.888 --> 01:01:05.474 line:90% position:50% align:center
control ourselves,

01:01:05.474 --> 01:01:10.354 line:90% position:50% align:center
our response to a situation,

01:01:10.354 --> 01:01:12.439 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to be peacemakers.

01:01:13.774 --> 01:01:18.487 line:90% position:50% align:center
And then an explanation, verse 19:

01:01:18.487 --> 01:01:22.074 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Do not avenge yourselves, beloved,

01:01:22.074 --> 01:01:24.576 line:90% position:50% align:center
but yield place to the wrath.”

01:01:24.576 --> 01:01:25.536 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why?

01:01:25.536 --> 01:01:29.414 line:90% position:50% align:center
“For it is written: ‘Vengeance is mine;

01:01:29.414 --> 01:01:32.834 line:90% position:50% align:center
I will repay,’ says Jehovah.”

01:01:33.961 --> 01:01:36.463 line:90% position:50% align:center
So the advice is this:

01:01:36.463 --> 01:01:38.590 line:90% position:50% align:center
Be a peacemaker,

01:01:38.590 --> 01:01:41.093 line:90% position:50% align:center
and leave wrath to God.

01:01:41.093 --> 01:01:45.722 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let him determine
if and when and upon whom

01:01:45.722 --> 01:01:48.016 line:90% position:50% align:center
vengeance will be brought.

01:01:49.685 --> 01:01:51.979 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s easy to say,

01:01:51.979 --> 01:01:55.399 line:90% position:50% align:center
but is it always easy to do?

01:01:55.399 --> 01:01:57.401 line:90% position:50% align:center
No.

01:01:57.401 --> 01:01:59.611 line:90% position:50% align:center
The example of King David

01:01:59.611 --> 01:02:03.073 line:90% position:50% align:center
can be very helpful to us.

01:02:03.073 --> 01:02:05.075 line:90% position:50% align:center
Through no fault of his own,

01:02:05.075 --> 01:02:08.078 line:90% position:50% align:center
David became the target

01:02:08.078 --> 01:02:12.416 line:90% position:50% align:center
of King Saul’s murderous hatred.

01:02:12.416 --> 01:02:14.626 line:90% position:50% align:center
And on several occasions,

01:02:14.626 --> 01:02:17.963 line:90% position:50% align:center
Saul tried to kill David.

01:02:17.963 --> 01:02:20.841 line:90% position:50% align:center
For several years David lived as a fugitive.

01:02:20.841 --> 01:02:24.886 line:90% position:50% align:center
But there were opportunities during that time

01:02:24.886 --> 01:02:29.808 line:90% position:50% align:center
for David to harm Saul, even to kill him.

01:02:30.976 --> 01:02:34.896 line:90% position:50% align:center
He could have justified that in his mind.

01:02:34.896 --> 01:02:37.482 line:90% position:50% align:center
But do you think had he done so

01:02:37.482 --> 01:02:41.403 line:90% position:50% align:center
it would have threatened his peace

01:02:41.403 --> 01:02:45.157 line:90% position:50% align:center
—his peace, especially, with Jehovah?

01:02:45.157 --> 01:02:48.368 line:90% position:50% align:center
We know that it would.

01:02:48.368 --> 01:02:51.371 line:90% position:50% align:center
So how did David respond?

01:02:51.371 --> 01:02:54.249 line:90% position:50% align:center
On one occasion, he said to his men:

01:02:54.249 --> 01:02:58.587 line:90% position:50% align:center
“It is unthinkable from Jehovah’s standpoint

01:02:58.587 --> 01:03:01.298 line:90% position:50% align:center
“that I should do such a thing to my lord,

01:03:01.298 --> 01:03:03.925 line:90% position:50% align:center
the anointed of Jehovah.”

01:03:05.969 --> 01:03:08.764 line:90% position:50% align:center
What helped David?

01:03:08.764 --> 01:03:11.224 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, he saw a bigger picture

01:03:11.224 --> 01:03:14.603 line:90% position:50% align:center
than David and Saul, didn’t he?

01:03:14.603 --> 01:03:18.023 line:90% position:50% align:center
He saw a picture with David, Saul,

01:03:18.023 --> 01:03:20.067 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Jehovah.

01:03:20.067 --> 01:03:23.612 line:90% position:50% align:center
He knew that if Saul needed to be corrected,

01:03:23.612 --> 01:03:27.783 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah would do it in his time and way.

01:03:27.783 --> 01:03:30.702 line:90% position:50% align:center
As a result, David was willing to be patient

01:03:30.702 --> 01:03:33.288 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he preserved his peace

01:03:33.288 --> 01:03:37.125 line:90% position:50% align:center
—his peace with God, his inner peace,

01:03:37.125 --> 01:03:40.003 line:90% position:50% align:center
and his peace with those around him.

01:03:40.003 --> 01:03:42.589 line:90% position:50% align:center
What a beautiful example!

01:03:42.589 --> 01:03:45.926 line:90% position:50% align:center
We can be sure that if we demonstrate

01:03:45.926 --> 01:03:48.095 line:90% position:50% align:center
our love for Jehovah

01:03:48.095 --> 01:03:52.974 line:90% position:50% align:center
by respecting his sovereignty
and waiting on him,

01:03:52.974 --> 01:03:56.144 line:90% position:50% align:center
we will enjoy peace as well.

01:03:57.437 --> 01:03:59.439 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah assures us

01:03:59.439 --> 01:04:02.567 line:90% position:50% align:center
that he will bless his people

01:04:02.567 --> 01:04:05.904 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he will bless us with peace.

01:04:05.904 --> 01:04:08.532 line:90% position:50% align:center
So let us be determined to love Jehovah

01:04:08.532 --> 01:04:12.244 line:90% position:50% align:center
with our whole heart, soul, and mind

01:04:12.244 --> 01:04:15.372 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to demonstrate our love for Jehovah

01:04:15.372 --> 01:04:20.001 line:90% position:50% align:center
by patiently waiting on him
and respecting his sovereignty

01:04:20.001 --> 01:04:22.045 line:90% position:50% align:center
—his way of doing things.

01:04:22.045 --> 01:04:24.256 line:90% position:50% align:center
If we do, we will enjoy

01:04:24.256 --> 01:04:27.718 line:90% position:50% align:center
the incomparable peace of God.

01:04:28.844 --> 01:04:32.973 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, Brother Ralph Walls,
a helper to the Personnel Committee,

01:04:32.973 --> 01:04:36.560 line:90% position:50% align:center
will present the next talk of this symposium,

01:04:36.560 --> 01:04:41.523 line:90% position:50% align:center
“How Love Leads to Genuine Peace
—Love of Neighbor.”

01:04:49.656 --> 01:04:53.326 line:90% position:50% align:center
Foretelling dominant traits
that would exist in the last days,

01:04:53.326 --> 01:04:57.873 line:90% position:50% align:center
2 Timothy chapter 3 says
that “men will be lovers of themselves.”

01:04:58.957 --> 01:05:02.544 line:90% position:50% align:center
Is it wrong for us to love ourselves?

01:05:02.544 --> 01:05:07.507 line:90% position:50% align:center
No, it’s normal, even necessary,
to have a healthy love of oneself.

01:05:07.507 --> 01:05:10.051 line:90% position:50% align:center
After all, Jesus said:

01:05:10.051 --> 01:05:14.222 line:90% position:50% align:center
“You must love your neighbor as yourself.”

01:05:15.307 --> 01:05:18.852 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we’ll talk more about that in a minute.

01:05:18.852 --> 01:05:20.854 line:90% position:50% align:center
However, the love mentioned here

01:05:20.854 --> 01:05:24.065 line:90% position:50% align:center
is distorted and selfish.

01:05:24.065 --> 01:05:26.985 line:90% position:50% align:center
And because it prevents love of neighbor,

01:05:26.985 --> 01:05:30.864 line:90% position:50% align:center
it becomes a barrier to peace.

01:05:30.864 --> 01:05:35.827 line:90% position:50% align:center
Some Bible scholars suggest that Paul
put love of self at the top of his list

01:05:35.827 --> 01:05:38.872 line:90% position:50% align:center
at 2 Timothy 3:1-5

01:05:38.872 --> 01:05:42.542 line:90% position:50% align:center
because all the remaining
negative characteristics in the list

01:05:42.542 --> 01:05:44.544 line:90% position:50% align:center
result from it.

01:05:44.544 --> 01:05:48.340 line:90% position:50% align:center
And those traits too are a barrier to peace.

01:05:48.340 --> 01:05:51.635 line:90% position:50% align:center
For example,
“not [being] open to any agreement”

01:05:51.635 --> 01:05:55.388 line:90% position:50% align:center
mentioned at 2 Timothy 3:3,

01:05:55.388 --> 01:05:58.475 line:90% position:50% align:center
often leads to “anger, wrath,

01:05:58.475 --> 01:06:02.187 line:90% position:50% align:center
screaming, and abusive speech.”

01:06:02.187 --> 01:06:04.356 line:90% position:50% align:center
Rather than bringing peace,

01:06:04.356 --> 01:06:08.610 line:90% position:50% align:center
such a lack of self-control
“stirs up strife.”

01:06:08.610 --> 01:06:11.279 line:90% position:50% align:center
On the other hand, love of neighbor

01:06:11.279 --> 01:06:14.407 line:90% position:50% align:center
has the opposite effect.

01:06:14.407 --> 01:06:17.619 line:90% position:50% align:center
It leads to genuine peace.

01:06:19.079 --> 01:06:23.416 line:90% position:50% align:center
Please turn to Matthew chapter 22,

01:06:23.416 --> 01:06:26.086 line:90% position:50% align:center
verse 36.

01:06:26.086 --> 01:06:29.923 line:90% position:50% align:center
One of the Pharisees versed in the Law

01:06:29.923 --> 01:06:32.843 line:90% position:50% align:center
tests Jesus:

01:06:32.843 --> 01:06:35.011 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Teacher,

01:06:35.011 --> 01:06:39.015 line:90% position:50% align:center
which is the greatest commandment
in the Law?”

01:06:40.183 --> 01:06:43.228 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus responded with the words in verse 37

01:06:43.228 --> 01:06:47.232 line:90% position:50% align:center
just considered at length
in the preceding talk:

01:06:47.232 --> 01:06:51.736 line:90% position:50% align:center
“You must love Jehovah your God.”

01:06:51.736 --> 01:06:54.906 line:90% position:50% align:center
But then, Jesus goes
beyond the original question

01:06:54.906 --> 01:06:56.741 line:90% position:50% align:center
and quotes a second commandment.

01:06:56.741 --> 01:06:59.786 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s read verse 39:

01:06:59.786 --> 01:07:02.706 line:90% position:50% align:center
“The second, like it, is this:

01:07:02.706 --> 01:07:06.793 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘You must love your neighbor as yourself.’”

01:07:08.211 --> 01:07:11.548 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus is saying that the two commandments

01:07:11.548 --> 01:07:14.467 line:90% position:50% align:center
—love of God and love of neighbor—

01:07:14.467 --> 01:07:16.636 line:90% position:50% align:center
are linked.

01:07:16.636 --> 01:07:21.349 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, how exactly would you define “neighbor”?

01:07:21.349 --> 01:07:24.185 line:90% position:50% align:center
Please turn to Luke chapter 10.

01:07:25.854 --> 01:07:29.566 line:90% position:50% align:center
Notice how Jesus answered this very question:

01:07:29.566 --> 01:07:32.360 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Who really is my neighbor?”

01:07:32.360 --> 01:07:35.488 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus responds clearly
with his renowned illustration

01:07:35.488 --> 01:07:37.782 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the neighborly Samaritan.

01:07:37.782 --> 01:07:41.661 line:90% position:50% align:center
In Jesus’ day, the Jews disdained Samaritans.

01:07:41.661 --> 01:07:46.374 line:90% position:50% align:center
Their attitude moved Jesus
to make a powerful point.

01:07:46.374 --> 01:07:49.586 line:90% position:50% align:center
In his illustration,
Jesus said that the Samaritan

01:07:49.586 --> 01:07:53.715 line:90% position:50% align:center
took extraordinary measures
to help a Jewish man.

01:07:53.715 --> 01:07:56.635 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Jew had fallen victim to robbers,

01:07:56.635 --> 01:07:59.721 line:90% position:50% align:center
and his own countrymen ignored him

01:07:59.721 --> 01:08:02.265 line:90% position:50% align:center
—leaving him half-dead.

01:08:02.265 --> 01:08:06.311 line:90% position:50% align:center
What Jesus said
must have stunned the audience.

01:08:06.311 --> 01:08:10.357 line:90% position:50% align:center
Luke 10:33, 34 reads:

01:08:12.150 --> 01:08:14.694 line:90% position:50% align:center
“But a certain Samaritan

01:08:14.694 --> 01:08:17.280 line:90% position:50% align:center
“traveling the road came upon him,

01:08:17.280 --> 01:08:21.534 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and at seeing him, he was moved with pity.

01:08:21.534 --> 01:08:24.871 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So he approached him
and bandaged his wounds,

01:08:24.871 --> 01:08:27.749 line:90% position:50% align:center
“pouring oil and wine on them.

01:08:27.749 --> 01:08:32.754 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Then he mounted him on his own animal
and brought him to an inn

01:08:32.754 --> 01:08:35.465 line:90% position:50% align:center
and took care of him.”

01:08:35.465 --> 01:08:40.095 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus then asked a penetrating question
in verse 36:

01:08:41.137 --> 01:08:43.139 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Who of these three

01:08:43.139 --> 01:08:46.977 line:90% position:50% align:center
seems to you
to have made himself neighbor?”

01:08:48.144 --> 01:08:50.146 line:90% position:50% align:center
His words recorded in verse 37

01:08:50.146 --> 01:08:53.692 line:90% position:50% align:center
are also directed to you and to me:

01:08:54.901 --> 01:08:57.779 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Go and do the same yourself.”

01:08:59.531 --> 01:09:01.616 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, our neighbors include

01:09:01.616 --> 01:09:05.245 line:90% position:50% align:center
not only our family members
and our Christian brothers and sisters

01:09:05.245 --> 01:09:09.416 line:90% position:50% align:center
but all whom we encounter from day to day.

01:09:09.416 --> 01:09:11.918 line:90% position:50% align:center
In other words, our love

01:09:11.918 --> 01:09:15.505 line:90% position:50% align:center
extends to those who are not of our own race,

01:09:15.505 --> 01:09:19.634 line:90% position:50% align:center
tribe, nationality, or religion.

01:09:19.634 --> 01:09:22.220 line:90% position:50% align:center
How do we show that love?

01:09:23.680 --> 01:09:27.851 line:90% position:50% align:center
Please turn with me to Romans chapter 13.

01:09:28.810 --> 01:09:31.980 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because we love our neighbor,

01:09:31.980 --> 01:09:36.276 line:90% position:50% align:center
we avoid conduct that disrupts peace.

01:09:37.277 --> 01:09:39.946 line:90% position:50% align:center
Instead, we strive to apply
the inspired counsel

01:09:39.946 --> 01:09:44.659 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Romans 13:8-10:

01:09:46.202 --> 01:09:51.082 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Do not owe anything to anyone
except to love one another;

01:09:51.082 --> 01:09:54.961 line:90% position:50% align:center
“for whoever loves his fellow man
has fulfilled the law.

01:09:54.961 --> 01:09:58.173 line:90% position:50% align:center
“For the law code,
‘You must not commit adultery,

01:09:58.173 --> 01:10:01.426 line:90% position:50% align:center
“you must not murder,
you must not steal, you must not covet,’

01:10:01.426 --> 01:10:04.512 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and whatever other commandment there is,

01:10:04.512 --> 01:10:07.140 line:90% position:50% align:center
“is summed up in this saying:

01:10:07.140 --> 01:10:11.478 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘You must love your neighbor as yourself.’

01:10:11.478 --> 01:10:14.981 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Love does not work evil to one’s neighbor;

01:10:14.981 --> 01:10:18.568 line:90% position:50% align:center
therefore, love is the law’s fulfillment.”

01:10:20.028 --> 01:10:23.198 line:90% position:50% align:center
That means that our responsibility
is to treat others

01:10:23.198 --> 01:10:25.742 line:90% position:50% align:center
in ways that promote peace.

01:10:25.742 --> 01:10:28.036 line:90% position:50% align:center
When others treat us unkindly,

01:10:28.036 --> 01:10:30.997 line:90% position:50% align:center
we endeavor to imitate Jesus.

01:10:30.997 --> 01:10:35.752 line:90% position:50% align:center
When he was being insulted,
he did not return the insult.

01:10:35.752 --> 01:10:39.172 line:90% position:50% align:center
When he was suffering,
he didn’t go threatening.

01:10:39.172 --> 01:10:42.842 line:90% position:50% align:center
Imitating the Prince of Peace
and the God of peace

01:10:42.842 --> 01:10:45.595 line:90% position:50% align:center
gives us inner peace.

01:10:47.263 --> 01:10:49.265 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the following dramatization,

01:10:49.265 --> 01:10:52.310 line:90% position:50% align:center
notice how a family benefits
from the apostle Paul’s example

01:10:52.310 --> 01:10:54.354 line:90% position:50% align:center
of displaying love of neighbor,

01:10:54.354 --> 01:10:56.648 line:90% position:50% align:center
even when provoked.

01:10:58.358 --> 01:10:59.359 line:90% position:50% align:center
What are you going to do?

01:10:59.359 --> 01:10:59.984 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’re just a coward.

01:10:59.984 --> 01:11:01.486 line:90% position:50% align:center
Man, all you do
is stand next to your little cart.

01:11:01.486 --> 01:11:02.237 line:90% position:50% align:center
You don’t do anything.

01:11:02.237 --> 01:11:02.862 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’re just a coward.

01:11:02.862 --> 01:11:03.613 line:90% position:50% align:center
You just stand next to your little cart.

01:11:03.613 --> 01:11:03.947 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’re just a coward.

01:11:03.947 --> 01:11:04.656 line:90% position:50% align:center
Ain’t no neutral.

01:11:04.656 --> 01:11:05.365 line:90% position:50% align:center
Stand up for your rights.

01:11:05.365 --> 01:11:06.074 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’re just a coward.

01:11:06.491 --> 01:11:07.826 line:90% position:50% align:center
Gabe,

01:11:07.826 --> 01:11:09.828 line:90% position:50% align:center
what happened today?

01:11:13.164 --> 01:11:16.209 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s just that I’ve been yelled at
in service before, but

01:11:17.335 --> 01:11:20.755 line:90% position:50% align:center
this time I wanted to—I don’t know.

01:11:22.132 --> 01:11:25.510 line:90% position:50% align:center
I wanted to go up to the girls
and smash their phones.

01:11:26.636 --> 01:11:28.638 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m so glad that you didn’t.

01:11:29.556 --> 01:11:31.850 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah, but

01:11:31.850 --> 01:11:34.727 line:90% position:50% align:center
I feel guilty

01:11:34.727 --> 01:11:37.689 line:90% position:50% align:center
because I was like—I was like so angry.

01:11:43.027 --> 01:11:44.863 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s OK.

01:11:46.114 --> 01:11:48.950 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s keep reading.

01:11:48.950 --> 01:11:51.995 line:90% position:50% align:center
We had left off in verse 26.

01:11:56.040 --> 01:12:00.044 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Suddenly a great earthquake occurred,

01:12:00.044 --> 01:12:03.256 line:90% position:50% align:center
“so that the foundations of the jail
were shaken.

01:12:03.256 --> 01:12:07.010 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Moreover, all the doors
were instantly opened,

01:12:07.010 --> 01:12:09.554 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and everyone’s bonds came loose.

01:12:09.554 --> 01:12:13.933 line:90% position:50% align:center
“When the jailer woke up
and saw that the prison doors were open,

01:12:13.933 --> 01:12:15.977 line:90% position:50% align:center
“he drew his sword

01:12:15.977 --> 01:12:18.062 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and was about to kill himself,

01:12:18.062 --> 01:12:21.524 line:90% position:50% align:center
“assuming that the prisoners had escaped.

01:12:21.524 --> 01:12:24.068 line:90% position:50% align:center
“But Paul called out with a loud voice:

01:12:24.068 --> 01:12:26.988 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Do not hurt yourself, for we are all here!’

01:12:27.780 --> 01:12:30.283 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So he asked for lights and rushed in,

01:12:31.868 --> 01:12:34.078 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and seized with trembling,

01:12:34.078 --> 01:12:36.331 line:90% position:50% align:center
he fell down before Paul and Silas.”

01:12:40.627 --> 01:12:43.046 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, think about what the jailer
had done to Paul.

01:12:49.093 --> 01:12:50.678 line:90% position:50% align:center
He could have hated him for it.

01:12:50.678 --> 01:12:52.096 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah, he could have.

01:12:53.973 --> 01:12:58.978 line:90% position:50% align:center
But I guess he saw the jailer’s pain
instead of just his own.

01:13:04.067 --> 01:13:06.194 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah, Paul loved his neighbor.

01:13:06.194 --> 01:13:09.072 line:90% position:50% align:center
He didn’t hold back
from trying to save his life.

01:13:20.583 --> 01:13:21.501 line:90% position:50% align:center
Come on, man.

01:13:27.590 --> 01:13:30.593 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey, how do you have the nerve
to keep coming out here?

01:13:32.720 --> 01:13:34.305 line:90% position:50% align:center
Look, you were right

01:13:34.305 --> 01:13:36.391 line:90% position:50% align:center
about what you said.

01:13:36.391 --> 01:13:40.186 line:90% position:50% align:center
No one should stand around
while other people suffer injustice.

01:13:40.186 --> 01:13:42.480 line:90% position:50% align:center
So do something. Fight like we do.

01:13:43.022 --> 01:13:45.024 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is my way of making a difference

01:13:45.024 --> 01:13:48.319 line:90% position:50% align:center
—the only way that I know
the world can really change.

01:13:48.319 --> 01:13:50.071 line:90% position:50% align:center
Come on, man, the Bible?

01:13:50.071 --> 01:13:54.242 line:90% position:50% align:center
Look, I get what you’re thinking,
but let me show you just one scripture.

01:13:55.076 --> 01:13:56.744 line:90% position:50% align:center
All right, one scripture.

01:13:56.744 --> 01:13:59.038 line:90% position:50% align:center
So this is a verse in the Bible
that convinced me

01:13:59.038 --> 01:14:01.082 line:90% position:50% align:center
of how I can make a difference.

01:14:01.082 --> 01:14:04.877 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s at Matthew 24:14.

01:14:04.877 --> 01:14:06.629 line:90% position:50% align:center
Here it says:

01:14:06.629 --> 01:14:09.632 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And this good news of the Kingdom
will be preached

01:14:09.632 --> 01:14:11.884 line:90% position:50% align:center
“in all the inhabited earth

01:14:11.884 --> 01:14:14.137 line:90% position:50% align:center
“for a witness to all the nations,

01:14:14.137 --> 01:14:16.889 line:90% position:50% align:center
and then the end will come.”

01:14:21.227 --> 01:14:24.605 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the dramatization, Paul could have reacted

01:14:24.605 --> 01:14:27.608 line:90% position:50% align:center
in a negative way toward the jailer.

01:14:27.608 --> 01:14:31.279 line:90% position:50% align:center
However, in spite of the way
he had been treated,

01:14:31.279 --> 01:14:34.324 line:90% position:50% align:center
he displayed neighborly love.

01:14:34.324 --> 01:14:36.784 line:90% position:50% align:center
And this had a powerful effect on the jailer

01:14:36.784 --> 01:14:39.078 line:90% position:50% align:center
and brought praise to Jehovah.

01:14:40.371 --> 01:14:43.416 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because we are imperfect,

01:14:43.416 --> 01:14:48.421 line:90% position:50% align:center
we must work hard
at cultivating love for our neighbor.

01:14:48.421 --> 01:14:53.176 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is illustrated in what happened
with the apostle Peter.

01:14:53.176 --> 01:14:56.679 line:90% position:50% align:center
Prior to becoming a follower of Jesus,

01:14:56.679 --> 01:15:00.558 line:90% position:50% align:center
he did not have fellowship
with non-Jewish people.

01:15:00.558 --> 01:15:03.186 line:90% position:50% align:center
But after he became a Christian,

01:15:03.186 --> 01:15:05.188 line:90% position:50% align:center
God taught him

01:15:05.188 --> 01:15:08.566 line:90% position:50% align:center
that division between Jews and Gentiles

01:15:08.566 --> 01:15:10.777 line:90% position:50% align:center
was not to continue,

01:15:10.777 --> 01:15:13.363 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Peter got the point.

01:15:13.363 --> 01:15:16.657 line:90% position:50% align:center
At Acts 10:34, 35,

01:15:16.657 --> 01:15:19.452 line:90% position:50% align:center
Peter is quoted as saying:

01:15:19.452 --> 01:15:23.831 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Now I truly understand
that God is not partial,

01:15:23.831 --> 01:15:28.836 line:90% position:50% align:center
“but in every nation the man who fears him
and does what is right

01:15:28.836 --> 01:15:32.131 line:90% position:50% align:center
is acceptable to him.”

01:15:32.131 --> 01:15:36.886 line:90% position:50% align:center
Peter even stayed in the newly converted
Gentiles’ home for days.

01:15:36.886 --> 01:15:39.764 line:90% position:50% align:center
And he continued the practice of eating

01:15:39.764 --> 01:15:43.142 line:90% position:50% align:center
with non-Jewish Christians.

01:15:43.142 --> 01:15:46.270 line:90% position:50% align:center
However, 13 years later

01:15:46.270 --> 01:15:48.773 line:90% position:50% align:center
while in Syrian Antioch,

01:15:48.773 --> 01:15:52.568 line:90% position:50% align:center
Peter suddenly stopped associating
with Gentile Christians.

01:15:52.568 --> 01:15:54.445 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why?

01:15:54.445 --> 01:15:56.781 line:90% position:50% align:center
He feared the reaction
of some Jewish Christians

01:15:56.781 --> 01:15:59.575 line:90% position:50% align:center
who were slow to accept change.

01:15:59.575 --> 01:16:04.038 line:90% position:50% align:center
This illustrates that prejudice
can be deeply rooted.

01:16:04.038 --> 01:16:07.542 line:90% position:50% align:center
It takes constant effort
to rid ourselves of it.

01:16:07.542 --> 01:16:11.754 line:90% position:50% align:center
But we must learn to view others impartially

01:16:11.754 --> 01:16:14.132 line:90% position:50% align:center
as Jehovah does.

01:16:14.132 --> 01:16:17.051 line:90% position:50% align:center
We want to treat others
as Jehovah treats them.

01:16:18.344 --> 01:16:22.098 line:90% position:50% align:center
In his Sermon on the Mount, Jesus said:

01:16:22.098 --> 01:16:24.642 line:90% position:50% align:center
“You heard that it was said:

01:16:24.642 --> 01:16:28.771 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘You must love your neighbor
and hate your enemy.’

01:16:28.771 --> 01:16:32.442 line:90% position:50% align:center
“However, I say to you:

01:16:32.442 --> 01:16:34.569 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Continue to love your enemies

01:16:34.569 --> 01:16:38.489 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to pray for those who persecute you.”

01:16:38.489 --> 01:16:42.326 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then, as recorded at Matthew chapter 5,

01:16:42.326 --> 01:16:45.121 line:90% position:50% align:center
and verse 45,

01:16:45.121 --> 01:16:48.332 line:90% position:50% align:center
he explains why we want to show
that type of love:

01:16:49.834 --> 01:16:54.505 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So that you may prove yourselves
sons of your Father who is in the heavens,

01:16:54.505 --> 01:16:58.217 line:90% position:50% align:center
“since he makes his sun rise
on both the wicked and the good

01:16:58.217 --> 01:17:01.304 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and makes it rain on both the righteous

01:17:01.304 --> 01:17:03.848 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the unrighteous.”

01:17:03.848 --> 01:17:06.851 line:90% position:50% align:center
This love produced by holy spirit

01:17:06.851 --> 01:17:11.856 line:90% position:50% align:center
is markedly different from the sort of love
that is common in the world.

01:17:11.856 --> 01:17:15.026 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s based on a higher principle.

01:17:15.026 --> 01:17:19.572 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus said even sinners
will follow a policy of like for like.

01:17:20.823 --> 01:17:25.828 line:90% position:50% align:center
But if we want to prove ourselves
sons of our “Father who is in the heavens,”

01:17:25.828 --> 01:17:28.164 line:90% position:50% align:center
we must be different.

01:17:28.164 --> 01:17:30.958 line:90% position:50% align:center
We welcome others

01:17:30.958 --> 01:17:34.420 line:90% position:50% align:center
as God and Christ have welcomed us.

01:17:34.420 --> 01:17:38.341 line:90% position:50% align:center
At Romans 15:7, the Bible says to us:

01:17:38.341 --> 01:17:40.718 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Welcome one another,

01:17:40.718 --> 01:17:44.889 line:90% position:50% align:center
just as Christ also welcomed you.”

01:17:44.889 --> 01:17:47.308 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Greek word used there conveys the idea

01:17:47.308 --> 01:17:50.353 line:90% position:50% align:center
of receiving someone kindly or hospitably

01:17:50.353 --> 01:17:53.773 line:90% position:50% align:center
—such as into one’s home
or circle of friends.

01:17:54.899 --> 01:17:58.736 line:90% position:50% align:center
Prejudice withers as love grows.

01:17:59.987 --> 01:18:02.448 line:90% position:50% align:center
Remember that at one time,

01:18:02.448 --> 01:18:07.119 line:90% position:50% align:center
we were all strangers, or foreigners,
not close to God.

01:18:07.119 --> 01:18:11.249 line:90% position:50% align:center
But Jehovah drew us to him

01:18:11.249 --> 01:18:13.834 line:90% position:50% align:center
with “cords of love.”

01:18:13.834 --> 01:18:17.088 line:90% position:50% align:center
Christ welcomed us.

01:18:17.088 --> 01:18:21.551 line:90% position:50% align:center
He opened the door, as it were,
so that we could become part of God’s family.

01:18:22.552 --> 01:18:26.264 line:90% position:50% align:center
Since Jesus has kindly accepted us

01:18:26.264 --> 01:18:28.766 line:90% position:50% align:center
as imperfect as we are,

01:18:28.766 --> 01:18:33.688 line:90% position:50% align:center
it should be unthinkable for us
to reject anyone else.

01:18:33.688 --> 01:18:35.481 line:90% position:50% align:center
Dear brothers and sisters,

01:18:35.481 --> 01:18:40.486 line:90% position:50% align:center
divisions, prejudice, and hostility
will doubtless increase in the world

01:18:40.486 --> 01:18:44.323 line:90% position:50% align:center
as we approach the end of this wicked system.

01:18:44.323 --> 01:18:47.159 line:90% position:50% align:center
As servants of Jehovah, though,

01:18:47.159 --> 01:18:51.372 line:90% position:50% align:center
we seek “the wisdom from above,”
which is impartial

01:18:51.372 --> 01:18:53.874 line:90% position:50% align:center
and promotes peace.

01:18:53.874 --> 01:18:56.002 line:90% position:50% align:center
We rejoice

01:18:56.002 --> 01:18:59.505 line:90% position:50% align:center
as we forge friendships
with people from other lands,

01:18:59.505 --> 01:19:01.507 line:90% position:50% align:center
accept cultural differences,

01:19:01.507 --> 01:19:05.428 line:90% position:50% align:center
and possibly even learn
the languages of others.

01:19:05.428 --> 01:19:07.430 line:90% position:50% align:center
When we do this,

01:19:07.430 --> 01:19:10.808 line:90% position:50% align:center
peace flows “just like a river”

01:19:10.808 --> 01:19:14.645 line:90% position:50% align:center
and justice “like the waves of the sea.”

01:19:14.645 --> 01:19:18.107 line:90% position:50% align:center
We “work what is good toward all,

01:19:18.107 --> 01:19:21.027 line:90% position:50% align:center
but especially [our brothers].”

01:19:21.027 --> 01:19:25.364 line:90% position:50% align:center
Love of neighbor moves us
to make sacrifices in behalf of others

01:19:25.364 --> 01:19:28.117 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to share the good news
at every opportunity.

01:19:29.619 --> 01:19:34.248 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our Master, Jesus, said:

01:19:34.248 --> 01:19:37.084 line:90% position:50% align:center
“This is my commandment,

01:19:37.084 --> 01:19:41.505 line:90% position:50% align:center
that you love one another
just as I have loved you.”

01:19:42.882 --> 01:19:47.470 line:90% position:50% align:center
What are the blessings
that come from love of neighbor?

01:19:47.470 --> 01:19:49.597 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus answers that

01:19:49.597 --> 01:19:52.683 line:90% position:50% align:center
at John chapter 15,

01:19:52.683 --> 01:19:55.186 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we’ll read verses 8 through 10,

01:19:58.981 --> 01:20:00.983 line:90% position:50% align:center
beginning with verse 8.

01:20:02.443 --> 01:20:04.445 line:90% position:50% align:center
Number one:

01:20:04.445 --> 01:20:08.658 line:90% position:50% align:center
“My father is glorified in this,

01:20:08.658 --> 01:20:11.702 line:90% position:50% align:center
“that you keep bearing much fruit

01:20:11.702 --> 01:20:14.538 line:90% position:50% align:center
and prove yourselves my disciples.”

01:20:15.706 --> 01:20:20.127 line:90% position:50% align:center
The second blessing, verse 9:

01:20:20.127 --> 01:20:24.256 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Just as the Father has loved me,
so I have loved you;

01:20:24.256 --> 01:20:26.967 line:90% position:50% align:center
“remain in my love.

01:20:26.967 --> 01:20:29.887 line:90% position:50% align:center
“If you observe my commandments,

01:20:29.887 --> 01:20:32.682 line:90% position:50% align:center
“you will remain in my love,

01:20:32.682 --> 01:20:35.976 line:90% position:50% align:center
“just as I have observed
the commandments of the Father

01:20:35.976 --> 01:20:38.771 line:90% position:50% align:center
and remain in his love.”

01:20:40.606 --> 01:20:44.068 line:90% position:50% align:center
Brother Robert Ciranko,
a helper to the Writing Committee,

01:20:44.068 --> 01:20:46.904 line:90% position:50% align:center
will now present the final talk
of this symposium,

01:20:46.904 --> 01:20:51.701 line:90% position:50% align:center
“How Love Leads to Genuine Peace
—Love for God’s Word.”

01:20:59.625 --> 01:21:04.380 line:90% position:50% align:center
Can you imagine a collection
of some 40 million books?

01:21:04.380 --> 01:21:06.549 line:90% position:50% align:center
They would fill more than 800 miles,

01:21:06.549 --> 01:21:09.552 line:90% position:50% align:center
or 1,300 kilometers, of bookshelves?

01:21:09.552 --> 01:21:12.513 line:90% position:50% align:center
And yet, that is what you can find
in what has been described

01:21:12.513 --> 01:21:15.725 line:90% position:50% align:center
as the largest library in the world

01:21:15.725 --> 01:21:18.686 line:90% position:50% align:center
—the Library of Congress
in Washington, D.C.,

01:21:18.686 --> 01:21:20.855 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the United States.

01:21:20.855 --> 01:21:24.316 line:90% position:50% align:center
Which book would you say
is the most worthwhile to read

01:21:24.316 --> 01:21:26.944 line:90% position:50% align:center
among all of those millions of volumes?

01:21:26.944 --> 01:21:29.989 line:90% position:50% align:center
We can let the apostle Paul
answer that question.

01:21:29.989 --> 01:21:33.701 line:90% position:50% align:center
In his second letter to Timothy
at 2 Timothy 3:15,

01:21:33.701 --> 01:21:37.204 line:90% position:50% align:center
he referred to “the holy writings,
which are able to make [us]

01:21:37.204 --> 01:21:41.751 line:90% position:50% align:center
wise for salvation
through faith in Christ Jesus.”

01:21:41.751 --> 01:21:45.629 line:90% position:50% align:center
He was referring, of course,
to God’s own written Word

01:21:45.629 --> 01:21:48.215 line:90% position:50% align:center
that we know as the Bible.

01:21:48.215 --> 01:21:52.803 line:90% position:50% align:center
The contents of this book can give us
the wisdom that we need to gain salvation,

01:21:52.803 --> 01:21:56.599 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that makes it
the most worthwhile book on earth.

01:21:57.725 --> 01:22:01.103 line:90% position:50% align:center
But how can a book have
such a profound effect on a person?

01:22:02.104 --> 01:22:05.149 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, when describing books
and their authors per se,

01:22:05.149 --> 01:22:08.235 line:90% position:50% align:center
the secular writer Gilbert Highet once stated

01:22:08.235 --> 01:22:11.322 line:90% position:50% align:center
that books are not “lumps of lifeless paper,

01:22:11.322 --> 01:22:14.658 line:90% position:50% align:center
“but minds alive on the shelves.

01:22:14.658 --> 01:22:16.660 line:90% position:50% align:center
“From each of them goes out
its own voice . . .

01:22:16.660 --> 01:22:20.122 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So by taking down one of these volumes
and opening it,

01:22:20.122 --> 01:22:23.626 line:90% position:50% align:center
“one can call into range
the voice of a man the author,

01:22:23.626 --> 01:22:25.961 line:90% position:50% align:center
“far distant in time and space,

01:22:25.961 --> 01:22:30.966 line:90% position:50% align:center
and hear him speaking to us,
mind to mind, heart to heart.”

01:22:30.966 --> 01:22:35.805 line:90% position:50% align:center
When we take this book, the Bible,
down off the shelf and open it,

01:22:35.805 --> 01:22:40.267 line:90% position:50% align:center
we are calling into range
the voice of its Author, Jehovah.

01:22:40.267 --> 01:22:44.647 line:90% position:50% align:center
And is he speaking to us
mind to mind, heart to heart?

01:22:44.647 --> 01:22:46.649 line:90% position:50% align:center
Indeed, he is.

01:22:46.649 --> 01:22:51.195 line:90% position:50% align:center
For example, at Jeremiah 29:11,
Jehovah tells us:

01:22:51.195 --> 01:22:55.324 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I well know the thoughts
that I am thinking toward you, . . .

01:22:55.324 --> 01:22:57.785 line:90% position:50% align:center
“thoughts of peace, and not of calamity,

01:22:57.785 --> 01:23:00.246 line:90% position:50% align:center
to give you a future and a hope.”

01:23:00.246 --> 01:23:03.707 line:90% position:50% align:center
And at Proverbs 27:11, Jehovah tells us:

01:23:03.707 --> 01:23:06.460 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Be wise . . . and make my heart rejoice,

01:23:06.460 --> 01:23:11.090 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that I can make a reply
to him who taunts me.”

01:23:11.090 --> 01:23:14.009 line:90% position:50% align:center
How grateful we are
that Jehovah has given us

01:23:14.009 --> 01:23:16.428 line:90% position:50% align:center
his precious Word, the Bible,

01:23:16.428 --> 01:23:19.431 line:90% position:50% align:center
that reveals his intimate thoughts
and feelings,

01:23:19.431 --> 01:23:21.433 line:90% position:50% align:center
that draws us close to him,

01:23:21.433 --> 01:23:25.479 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that teaches us
how to gain everlasting life!

01:23:25.479 --> 01:23:29.066 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because we love Jehovah,
we also love and cherish

01:23:29.066 --> 01:23:33.404 line:90% position:50% align:center
what he tells us
through the pages of his written Word.

01:23:33.404 --> 01:23:36.031 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that is exactly how the psalmist felt

01:23:36.031 --> 01:23:38.659 line:90% position:50% align:center
who wrote the 119th Psalm.

01:23:38.659 --> 01:23:42.872 line:90% position:50% align:center
Please open your Bible to Psalm 119,

01:23:42.872 --> 01:23:45.457 line:90% position:50% align:center
and find verse 161.

01:23:45.457 --> 01:23:49.670 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s Psalm 119:161.

01:23:49.670 --> 01:23:52.923 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the latter part, it says:

01:23:52.923 --> 01:23:57.511 line:90% position:50% align:center
“But my heart stands in awe of your words.”

01:23:57.511 --> 01:24:02.474 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now see what more he wrote
in verses 167 and 168:

01:24:03.559 --> 01:24:07.229 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I keep your reminders,
and I love them dearly.

01:24:07.229 --> 01:24:10.524 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I observe your orders and your reminders,

01:24:10.524 --> 01:24:14.153 line:90% position:50% align:center
for you are aware of all that I do.”

01:24:15.279 --> 01:24:19.033 line:90% position:50% align:center
This Bible writer did not view
God’s orders and reminders

01:24:19.033 --> 01:24:23.913 line:90% position:50% align:center
as just a list of cold, legalistic statutes.

01:24:23.913 --> 01:24:26.582 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we can be sure
that he did not consider them

01:24:26.582 --> 01:24:28.584 line:90% position:50% align:center
to be burdensome.

01:24:28.584 --> 01:24:31.754 line:90% position:50% align:center
Instead, he knew that they formed the basis

01:24:31.754 --> 01:24:34.173 line:90% position:50% align:center
for the best life possible.

01:24:34.173 --> 01:24:37.927 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that is why he not only wanted
to learn God’s orders,

01:24:37.927 --> 01:24:41.639 line:90% position:50% align:center
but he also desired to observe,
or obey, them.

01:24:42.765 --> 01:24:47.770 line:90% position:50% align:center
The psalmist believed that God’s Word
is the one thing worth studying,

01:24:47.770 --> 01:24:51.023 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that because of knowing
God’s orders and reminders,

01:24:51.023 --> 01:24:53.150 line:90% position:50% align:center
we are far wiser than people

01:24:53.150 --> 01:24:57.112 line:90% position:50% align:center
who know everything else
except God’s Word.

01:24:57.112 --> 01:25:04.036 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now look at what more he wrote in verse 165:

01:25:04.036 --> 01:25:08.415 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Abundant peace
belongs to those who love your law;

01:25:08.415 --> 01:25:12.044 line:90% position:50% align:center
nothing can make them stumble.”

01:25:12.044 --> 01:25:16.507 line:90% position:50% align:center
Herein lies a major reason
why we love God’s Word:

01:25:16.507 --> 01:25:20.469 line:90% position:50% align:center
Abiding by it leads to genuine peace.

01:25:20.469 --> 01:25:22.888 line:90% position:50% align:center
Everyone longs for peace in their life,

01:25:22.888 --> 01:25:27.559 line:90% position:50% align:center
and through the pages of the Bible,
we learn how to attain it.

01:25:27.559 --> 01:25:30.646 line:90% position:50% align:center
That is why we choose to live by God’s Word

01:25:30.646 --> 01:25:33.774 line:90% position:50% align:center
even in the face of the trials
that arise in our life

01:25:33.774 --> 01:25:38.445 line:90% position:50% align:center
—some of which may try to steal away
our peace of mind and heart.

01:25:38.445 --> 01:25:42.282 line:90% position:50% align:center
And yet, Jehovah knows what we
are going through every day of our lives

01:25:42.282 --> 01:25:44.660 line:90% position:50% align:center
and stands ready to help us.

01:25:46.120 --> 01:25:48.706 line:90% position:50% align:center
If we love and obey Jehovah’s Word,

01:25:48.706 --> 01:25:53.544 line:90% position:50% align:center
we will not be stumbled spiritually
by what someone else does or says

01:25:53.544 --> 01:25:56.880 line:90% position:50% align:center
or by any other matter or situation in life.

01:25:57.840 --> 01:26:01.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
But how does love for God’s Word
lead to such peace

01:26:01.135 --> 01:26:04.388 line:90% position:50% align:center
and keep us from stumbling?

01:26:04.388 --> 01:26:06.932 line:90% position:50% align:center
We know
that “all scripture is inspired of God,”

01:26:06.932 --> 01:26:11.603 line:90% position:50% align:center
making the Bible the most reliable guide
for every aspect of life.

01:26:11.603 --> 01:26:16.316 line:90% position:50% align:center
After all, his wisdom
is infinitely superior to our own.

01:26:16.316 --> 01:26:18.861 line:90% position:50% align:center
Reading the Bible enables us
to look at matters

01:26:18.861 --> 01:26:21.864 line:90% position:50% align:center
from God’s elevated point of view.

01:26:21.864 --> 01:26:25.534 line:90% position:50% align:center
It is just as the prophet Isaiah wrote

01:26:25.534 --> 01:26:29.038 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Isaiah 55:8, 9.

01:26:29.038 --> 01:26:31.248 line:90% position:50% align:center
If you’d like to open to that, please

01:26:31.248 --> 01:26:34.543 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Isaiah 55:8, 9.

01:26:36.128 --> 01:26:40.299 line:90% position:50% align:center
He wrote: “‘For my thoughts
are not your thoughts,

01:26:40.299 --> 01:26:44.678 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and your ways are not my ways,’
declares Jehovah.

01:26:44.678 --> 01:26:46.930 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘For as the heavens
are higher than the earth,

01:26:46.930 --> 01:26:49.767 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘so my ways are higher than your ways

01:26:49.767 --> 01:26:52.895 line:90% position:50% align:center
and my thoughts than your thoughts.’”

01:26:53.979 --> 01:26:57.274 line:90% position:50% align:center
Just imagine
—Jehovah’s thoughts and language

01:26:57.274 --> 01:27:01.361 line:90% position:50% align:center
must be vastly superior to those of humans.

01:27:01.361 --> 01:27:04.865 line:90% position:50% align:center
When he communicates with us,
as he does through the pages of the Bible,

01:27:04.865 --> 01:27:08.702 line:90% position:50% align:center
he simplifies how he expresses his thoughts

01:27:08.702 --> 01:27:11.121 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that we can understand them.

01:27:11.121 --> 01:27:13.832 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then as we take in all that Jehovah says,

01:27:13.832 --> 01:27:17.086 line:90% position:50% align:center
we can let his thinking guide our thinking.

01:27:18.378 --> 01:27:22.424 line:90% position:50% align:center
Reading the Bible
can be likened to peering into a mirror

01:27:22.424 --> 01:27:25.260 line:90% position:50% align:center
because its message
has the power to allow us

01:27:25.260 --> 01:27:28.222 line:90% position:50% align:center
to see ourselves as we really are

01:27:28.222 --> 01:27:30.641 line:90% position:50% align:center
and it shows us where adjustments
are needed

01:27:30.641 --> 01:27:32.976 line:90% position:50% align:center
in our attitude and conduct.

01:27:34.937 --> 01:27:38.690 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thus far in this symposium,
we have seen how this can actually work.

01:27:38.690 --> 01:27:41.944 line:90% position:50% align:center
We have seen two dramatizations
of a widowed mother

01:27:41.944 --> 01:27:46.031 line:90% position:50% align:center
using the Bible to help her teenage children
avoid being stumbled

01:27:46.031 --> 01:27:49.910 line:90% position:50% align:center
by other young people
who had been harassing them.

01:27:49.910 --> 01:27:53.122 line:90% position:50% align:center
Remember, her son, Gabe,
had been called a coward

01:27:53.122 --> 01:27:55.374 line:90% position:50% align:center
by a couple of tough-looking youths

01:27:55.374 --> 01:27:58.252 line:90% position:50% align:center
while he was engaged in public witnessing.

01:27:58.252 --> 01:28:01.380 line:90% position:50% align:center
And her daughter, Olivia,
had been chided by other girls

01:28:01.380 --> 01:28:06.385 line:90% position:50% align:center
for not being interested in dating
one of the guys in her class.

01:28:06.385 --> 01:28:11.098 line:90% position:50% align:center
Their mother used what Jehovah inspired
the apostle Paul to write about

01:28:11.098 --> 01:28:13.350 line:90% position:50% align:center
with his ordeal in prison

01:28:13.350 --> 01:28:17.104 line:90% position:50% align:center
to show how he was able
to preserve his peace

01:28:17.104 --> 01:28:19.731 line:90% position:50% align:center
in a very difficult situation.

01:28:19.731 --> 01:28:24.611 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that, in turn, helped Olivia and Gabe
to safeguard their own peace.

01:28:25.779 --> 01:28:29.783 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s see what more the mother finds
in the Bible to help Olivia

01:28:29.783 --> 01:28:34.454 line:90% position:50% align:center
avoid being stumbled into conduct
that could rob her of peace.

01:28:35.956 --> 01:28:37.791 line:90% position:50% align:center
Guess who just walked in?

01:28:37.791 --> 01:28:38.458 line:90% position:50% align:center
Olivia.

01:28:38.458 --> 01:28:39.710 line:90% position:50% align:center
And there’s Jake.

01:28:39.710 --> 01:28:40.377 line:90% position:50% align:center
Would she ever?

01:28:40.377 --> 01:28:40.919 line:90% position:50% align:center
You know she’s wild.

01:28:40.919 --> 01:28:42.588 line:90% position:50% align:center
I don’t even think she likes guys.

01:28:42.588 --> 01:28:43.463 line:90% position:50% align:center
What if she’s into girls?

01:28:43.463 --> 01:28:45.215 line:90% position:50% align:center
I bet she’s still a virgin.

01:28:47.634 --> 01:28:49.678 line:90% position:50% align:center
Olivia, what are you thinking?

01:28:52.181 --> 01:28:55.642 line:90% position:50% align:center
I don’t—I don’t know how they could do that.

01:28:55.642 --> 01:28:57.686 line:90% position:50% align:center
I don’t even follow them.

01:28:58.395 --> 01:29:00.397 line:90% position:50% align:center
If this doesn’t stop,

01:29:02.774 --> 01:29:04.818 line:90% position:50% align:center
I don’t know if I can . . .

01:29:07.654 --> 01:29:09.948 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’re strong, OK.

01:29:09.948 --> 01:29:11.950 line:90% position:50% align:center
You just can’t let them get to you.

01:29:18.373 --> 01:29:20.751 line:90% position:50% align:center
It feels out of your control, doesn’t it?

01:29:33.096 --> 01:29:36.516 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey, I think we need another Bible example.

01:29:37.768 --> 01:29:40.729 line:90% position:50% align:center
Remember when we studied
about the Shulammite girl?

01:29:44.775 --> 01:29:46.568 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah, I remember.

01:29:47.152 --> 01:29:49.154 line:90% position:50% align:center
And who was pressuring her?

01:29:52.491 --> 01:29:54.534 line:90% position:50% align:center
Solomon.

01:29:59.206 --> 01:30:02.459 line:90% position:50% align:center
But she wasn’t interested in him,

01:30:02.459 --> 01:30:06.630 line:90% position:50% align:center
just like I’m not interested
in that boy Jake, so . . .

01:30:07.547 --> 01:30:09.508 line:90% position:50% align:center
But it wasn’t just him;

01:30:09.508 --> 01:30:13.136 line:90% position:50% align:center
there were the daughters of Jerusalem
in Solomon’s court.

01:30:15.639 --> 01:30:18.308 line:90% position:50% align:center
They urged her to accept his attentions.

01:30:20.978 --> 01:30:23.814 line:90% position:50% align:center
But do you remember what she said

01:30:23.814 --> 01:30:26.024 line:90% position:50% align:center
in Song of Solomon chapter 2?

01:30:29.236 --> 01:30:31.280 line:90% position:50% align:center
It says: “I put you under oath,

01:30:31.280 --> 01:30:33.407 line:90% position:50% align:center
“O daughters of Jerusalem,

01:30:33.407 --> 01:30:36.159 line:90% position:50% align:center
“by the gazelles and the does of the field:

01:30:36.159 --> 01:30:40.038 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Do not try to awaken or arouse love in me

01:30:40.038 --> 01:30:42.040 line:90% position:50% align:center
until it feels inclined.”

01:30:43.625 --> 01:30:47.296 line:90% position:50% align:center
So despite all of the pressure,
who was really in control?

01:30:49.965 --> 01:30:52.009 line:90% position:50% align:center
She was.

01:30:53.302 --> 01:30:57.055 line:90% position:50% align:center
No one was going to push her
into something that she didn’t want to do.

01:31:00.434 --> 01:31:04.021 line:90% position:50% align:center
She even said: “I am a wall.”

01:31:06.440 --> 01:31:08.483 line:90% position:50% align:center
You have the same power.

01:31:11.320 --> 01:31:15.741 line:90% position:50% align:center
And if you believe that,
it’ll change how you handle the pressure.

01:31:18.785 --> 01:31:20.037 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now give me a hug.

01:31:32.424 --> 01:31:35.260 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey, guys, update on yesterday’s topic.

01:31:35.260 --> 01:31:37.095 line:90% position:50% align:center
I guess she still needs a man.

01:31:37.095 --> 01:31:38.764 line:90% position:50% align:center
She needs something.

01:31:43.810 --> 01:31:45.854 line:90% position:50% align:center
I just posted it. Go like my video.

01:31:47.481 --> 01:31:50.192 line:90% position:50% align:center
All they want is to see me give in.

01:31:51.234 --> 01:31:54.780 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey, guys, update on yesterday’s topic.
I guess she still needs . . .

01:31:55.447 --> 01:31:58.283 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why would I give them the satisfaction?

01:31:59.117 --> 01:32:01.787 line:90% position:50% align:center
My peace comes from doing the right thing.

01:32:03.205 --> 01:32:05.624 line:90% position:50% align:center
Nobody can make me stumble.

01:32:10.670 --> 01:32:12.798 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I am a wall.”

01:32:26.520 --> 01:32:29.856 line:90% position:50% align:center
Olivia’s mother thought
of another inspired Bible example,

01:32:29.856 --> 01:32:32.776 line:90% position:50% align:center
that of the Shulammite girl
who was being urged

01:32:32.776 --> 01:32:37.322 line:90% position:50% align:center
by the young women in Solomon’s court
to accept his amorous attentions.

01:32:37.322 --> 01:32:41.284 line:90% position:50% align:center
But despite the pressure,
the Shulammite girl remained in control

01:32:41.284 --> 01:32:45.956 line:90% position:50% align:center
for no one was going to push her
into something that she did not want to do.

01:32:45.956 --> 01:32:49.751 line:90% position:50% align:center
Olivia got the point
as she thought to herself:

01:32:49.751 --> 01:32:52.254 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘My peace comes from doing the right thing.

01:32:52.254 --> 01:32:55.882 line:90% position:50% align:center
Nobody can make me stumble. I am a wall.’

01:32:57.092 --> 01:33:01.430 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s obvious that the mother
had a real love for God’s Word, knew it well,

01:33:01.430 --> 01:33:06.393 line:90% position:50% align:center
and calmly and skillfully used it
to guide the thinking of her children

01:33:06.393 --> 01:33:09.020 line:90% position:50% align:center
to keep them from stumbling.

01:33:10.564 --> 01:33:13.942 line:90% position:50% align:center
So many people these days
put God’s Word out of their mind

01:33:13.942 --> 01:33:16.903 line:90% position:50% align:center
to prevent it from influencing their life.

01:33:16.903 --> 01:33:20.907 line:90% position:50% align:center
But as the world’s morals decline,
we must stick loyally to God’s Word

01:33:20.907 --> 01:33:24.870 line:90% position:50% align:center
to conform our conduct
to his pure and holy thinking

01:33:24.870 --> 01:33:28.999 line:90% position:50% align:center
and strengthen our determination
to live by his standards.

01:33:30.709 --> 01:33:34.171 line:90% position:50% align:center
That is just what the apostle Paul
urged us to do

01:33:34.171 --> 01:33:37.257 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Romans 12:2.

01:33:37.257 --> 01:33:41.678 line:90% position:50% align:center
If you would turn there, please
—Romans 12:2.

01:33:42.554 --> 01:33:44.556 line:90% position:50% align:center
Paul wrote:

01:33:44.556 --> 01:33:48.143 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And stop being molded
by this system of things,

01:33:48.143 --> 01:33:51.855 line:90% position:50% align:center
“but be transformed
by making your mind over,

01:33:51.855 --> 01:33:56.485 line:90% position:50% align:center
“so that you may prove to yourselves
the good and acceptable

01:33:56.485 --> 01:33:59.446 line:90% position:50% align:center
and perfect will of God.”

01:33:59.446 --> 01:34:03.033 line:90% position:50% align:center
God’s Word strengthens us
to resist conforming

01:34:03.033 --> 01:34:05.368 line:90% position:50% align:center
to the corrupting practices of Satan’s world

01:34:05.368 --> 01:34:08.914 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to suppress temptations
toward wrongdoing.

01:34:09.915 --> 01:34:12.000 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, as we prove to ourselves

01:34:12.000 --> 01:34:15.295 line:90% position:50% align:center
that the will of God is good and perfect,

01:34:15.295 --> 01:34:17.380 line:90% position:50% align:center
then we should also accept

01:34:17.380 --> 01:34:20.842 line:90% position:50% align:center
that loyally obeying God
is the best way of living.

01:34:20.842 --> 01:34:24.304 line:90% position:50% align:center
There is a direct connection
between heeding Scriptural teachings

01:34:24.304 --> 01:34:28.391 line:90% position:50% align:center
and obeying or enjoying genuine peace.

01:34:29.559 --> 01:34:33.396 line:90% position:50% align:center
However, for Jehovah’s Word
to have such power in our lives,

01:34:33.396 --> 01:34:36.441 line:90% position:50% align:center
we need to read the Bible every day

01:34:36.441 --> 01:34:40.445 line:90% position:50% align:center
and meditate on why its counsel
is beneficial.

01:34:40.445 --> 01:34:42.656 line:90% position:50% align:center
That means reading it at a pace

01:34:42.656 --> 01:34:46.785 line:90% position:50% align:center
that allows us to ponder
on what we are reading.

01:34:46.785 --> 01:34:49.871 line:90% position:50% align:center
And doing this helps to fix in our minds
the portions

01:34:49.871 --> 01:34:52.749 line:90% position:50% align:center
that are especially helpful to us.

01:34:52.749 --> 01:34:56.962 line:90% position:50% align:center
When asked why he reads the Bible
every day,

01:34:56.962 --> 01:34:59.047 line:90% position:50% align:center
one Christian replied:

01:34:59.047 --> 01:35:01.967 line:90% position:50% align:center
“If I repeatedly pray to Jehovah
during the day

01:35:01.967 --> 01:35:04.511 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and expect him to hear me,

01:35:04.511 --> 01:35:09.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
“why shouldn’t I also listen to God
by reading his Word every day?

01:35:09.432 --> 01:35:11.476 line:90% position:50% align:center
“If we want to be a good friend,

01:35:11.476 --> 01:35:14.396 line:90% position:50% align:center
why would we do all the talking?”

01:35:14.396 --> 01:35:17.190 line:90% position:50% align:center
He makes a very good point, doesn’t he?

01:35:17.190 --> 01:35:20.944 line:90% position:50% align:center
By reading the Bible,
we are listening to Jehovah,

01:35:20.944 --> 01:35:24.781 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that is how we get
his viewpoint on matters.

01:35:24.781 --> 01:35:29.661 line:90% position:50% align:center
So do you allow God
to speak to you every day?

01:35:30.996 --> 01:35:33.707 line:90% position:50% align:center
We can measure
how effective our Bible reading is

01:35:33.707 --> 01:35:37.460 line:90% position:50% align:center
by the influence it has
on our attitude and conduct.

01:35:37.460 --> 01:35:41.715 line:90% position:50% align:center
When our peace is disturbed,
we can look into the source of divine wisdom

01:35:41.715 --> 01:35:44.384 line:90% position:50% align:center
for God’s guidance.

01:35:44.384 --> 01:35:47.095 line:90% position:50% align:center
Speaking prophetically of anointed Christians

01:35:47.095 --> 01:35:50.390 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Isaiah 54:13, the prophet wrote:

01:35:50.390 --> 01:35:53.893 line:90% position:50% align:center
“All your sons will be taught by Jehovah,

01:35:53.893 --> 01:35:57.188 line:90% position:50% align:center
and [their] peace . . . will be abundant.”

01:35:57.188 --> 01:36:01.318 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, those words apply in principle
to Christ’s other sheep as well.

01:36:01.318 --> 01:36:05.030 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thankfully, when Christ’s anointed brothers,
“the faithful and discreet slave,”

01:36:05.030 --> 01:36:08.950 line:90% position:50% align:center
prepare spiritual food for us,
such as this convention program,

01:36:08.950 --> 01:36:13.955 line:90% position:50% align:center
they hold firmly to Jehovah’s Word
and they never water it down.

01:36:13.955 --> 01:36:16.833 line:90% position:50% align:center
We always receive spiritual instruction

01:36:16.833 --> 01:36:20.629 line:90% position:50% align:center
that upholds Jehovah’s high moral standards,

01:36:20.629 --> 01:36:23.548 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we are blessed with abundant peace

01:36:23.548 --> 01:36:26.718 line:90% position:50% align:center
when we accept Jehovah’s instruction.

01:36:28.219 --> 01:36:31.598 line:90% position:50% align:center
Isaiah penned another prophecy
that is being fulfilled today,

01:36:31.598 --> 01:36:35.268 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we find that at Isaiah 2:2-4.

01:36:35.268 --> 01:36:37.270 line:90% position:50% align:center
He saw in a vision of the last days

01:36:37.270 --> 01:36:40.315 line:90% position:50% align:center
people from all the nations
streaming to true worship.

01:36:40.315 --> 01:36:42.317 line:90% position:50% align:center
And for what reason?

01:36:42.317 --> 01:36:44.361 line:90% position:50% align:center
Isaiah wrote of Jehovah:

01:36:44.361 --> 01:36:46.988 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He will instruct us about his ways,

01:36:46.988 --> 01:36:49.866 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we will walk in his paths.”

01:36:49.866 --> 01:36:51.868 line:90% position:50% align:center
And in what would this result?

01:36:51.868 --> 01:36:55.538 line:90% position:50% align:center
So that “they will beat their swords
into plowshares

01:36:55.538 --> 01:36:57.666 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and their spears into pruning shears.

01:36:57.666 --> 01:37:00.543 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Nation will not lift up sword
against nation,

01:37:00.543 --> 01:37:04.923 line:90% position:50% align:center
nor will they learn war anymore.”

01:37:04.923 --> 01:37:09.511 line:90% position:50% align:center
In his goodness, Jehovah is willing
to teach us imperfect humans

01:37:09.511 --> 01:37:13.973 line:90% position:50% align:center
how to achieve genuine,
abundant peace earth wide.

01:37:13.973 --> 01:37:17.268 line:90% position:50% align:center
And he does that through the pages
of his own written Word.

01:37:17.268 --> 01:37:20.939 line:90% position:50% align:center
What a privilege it is
to be taught by our God!

01:37:21.981 --> 01:37:26.486 line:90% position:50% align:center
No matter what problem may threaten
the peace of our personal life,

01:37:26.486 --> 01:37:29.739 line:90% position:50% align:center
our family, or our congregation,

01:37:29.739 --> 01:37:34.285 line:90% position:50% align:center
we are confident that the solution
can be found in the Bible.

01:37:34.285 --> 01:37:36.788 line:90% position:50% align:center
And as we have learned from this symposium,

01:37:36.788 --> 01:37:41.751 line:90% position:50% align:center
our continued love for Jehovah,
for our neighbor, and for God’s Word

01:37:41.751 --> 01:37:45.338 line:90% position:50% align:center
will lead to our enjoying everlasting peace

01:37:45.338 --> 01:37:47.340 line:90% position:50% align:center
in God’s new world.

01:37:49.342 --> 01:37:51.678 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thank you, brothers, for teaching us

01:37:51.678 --> 01:37:55.181 line:90% position:50% align:center
how love motivates our pursuit of peace.

01:37:56.391 --> 01:38:01.229 line:90% position:50% align:center
Each of us now has an opportunity
to praise Jehovah with song.

01:38:01.229 --> 01:38:04.899 line:90% position:50% align:center
We will sing song number 24, entitled

01:38:04.899 --> 01:38:07.277 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Come to Jehovah’s Mountain.”

01:38:07.277 --> 01:38:09.070 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s song number 24.

